org.threadly.concurrent.future

Class ClearOnGetSettableListenableFuture<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.concurrent.future.SettableListenableFuture<T>
      • org.threadly.concurrent.future.ClearOnGetSettableListenableFuture<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The result object type returned by this future
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Future<T>, FutureCallback<T>, ListenableFuture<T>

    public class ClearOnGetSettableListenableFuture<T>
extends SettableListenableFuture<T>

    This is a slight modification to the behavior of the parent class SettableListenableFuture. In this implementation, after the first get() call the stored result will be cleared (thus allowing it to be available for garbage collection).

    Because the result is cleared after the first get() call, get() can ONLY BE INVOKED ONCE. Additional invocations will result in a IllegalStateException. This implementation only makes sense in specific uses cases (for example when chaining SettableListenableFuture's together).

    In addition only one callback can be added, and if a callback is added you can not call get(). That single callback will clear the result (functioning like a get() call).

    Since:
    3.3.0
